    "meaning": "without doing ~; to do [B] without doing [A]",
    "structure": "Not, Negative plain form",
    "explanation": "This is used after a verb to request to the listener to not do something.You can remove the ください (kudasai), to just say ないで (naide), which is more casual.Be careful to not confuse this with the other ないで (naide) meaning.Example A) Please don’t行かないでください。ika naide kudasai.Please don’t go!Example B)それを食べないでください。sore o tabe naide kudasai.Please don’t eat that.Other NotesTo say the opposite, “please do”, use てください (te kudasai)See all related grammar.",
    "jlptLevel": "N5",
    "lessonNumber": 4,
    "lessonTitle": "More Verb Forms",
    "examples": [
